The paper also presents theoretical advancements in regret minimization algorithms, which are relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper uses extensive-form games and game decomposition methods, which are relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation and efficiency of the regret minimization algorithm, which is relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
